*[toxcore/friend_connection.c, line 842 at r1](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/296#-KYSEGFaBqhCo2fFmvuZ:-KYSEGFaBqhCo2fFmvu_:bdwna8o) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/8f320c8714ba7c5bf742e42d91a95227708f76c0/toxcore/friend_connection.c#L842)):*
> ```C
> static void LANdiscovery(Friend_Connections *fr_c)
> {
>     if (fr_c->last_LANdiscovery + LAN_DISCOVERY_INTERVAL < unix_time() && fr_c->dht->local_discovery_enabled) {
> ```

Why is this check necessary? This looks like a hacky way of disabling LAN discovery. Instead of disabling LAN discovery by adding a condition into `LANdiscovery()` function, it should be disabled so that this function wouldn't be called by toxcore in the first place.

